Overview

This document aims to provide the message specifications for connecting between POS machines and KEDC devices. The message specifications in this document are based on (1) Hypercom and (2) POSNET standards.

Message Structure

The messages transmitted between the POS and Terminal will use the following structure:

Field Bytes Value Comment
STX 1 02h or 82 Start of Text: This character indicates the start of a frame.

For normal Transaction, Start Text must set as 02
For [E-TAX] Transaction, Start Text must set as 82
LLLL 2 Length of the MESSAGE DATA in BCD format. Example: 256 bytes as 02h 56h.

[E-TAX] : The Length of E-TAX Message is required to send in base 16 numbers. This means POS is required to convert from decimal into base 16 numbers for both request and response.
For example, a length of 256 bytes will be convert to base 16 and transmitted as 0100. The LLLL field allows the inclusion of binary data in the message. The maximum alwable value for LLL will depend on the implementation.
MESSAGE DATA Variable The message data consists of a Transport Header, a Presentation Header, and Field Data.
ETX 1 03h End of Text: Indicates the end of a message.
LRC 1 Longitudinal Redundancy Character: Calculated by XOR-ing of each character from STX to ETX.

MESSAGE DATA

The message data consists of three different components, as shown in the following diagram.

Transport Header

The first data in the Message Data is the Transport Header. The Transport Header provides flexibility in message routing, and allows more than one application to use the same network.

The the Transport Header are consisted of the following fields arranged in the following order.

The fields are described below.

Field Bytes Value Use
Transport Header Type 2 60 The type of application which this message is used for. A value of ‘60’ defines an Application Message
Transport Destination 4 0000 Allows POS to select the merge destination. If this value is ‘0000’, the Terminal will determine the correct destination to route the message from its internal tables.
Transport Source 4 0000 The first two digits of this field must be ‘00’. The next two digits can be used by the POS for any purpose. Typically this will be ‘00’, but if there are multiple devices connected to the POS, this field can be used to identify the device that generate the original request.

Presentation Header

The next data in the Message Data is the Presentation Header. The Presentation Header indicates that is a request or a response, the transaction code, a response code, and an indication if there are more messages associated with this message.

The fields are described as shown below.

Field Bytes Value Use
Format Version 1 1 Indicates format of the supported messages
Request-Response Indicator 1 Type of message
'0' This message is a request message which requires a response
'1' This message is a response message
'2' This message is a request message which does not require a response
Transaction Code 2 Identifies the type of transaction. The possible values can be found in 'Transaction Code' section.
Response code 2 Identifies the result of the transaction. Response code should set to '00' for all request messages. The possible values can be found in 'Transaction Code' section.
More Indicator 1 '0' This is the last message for this transaction.
'1' There is another message following this one with more field data for this transaction.
Field Separator 1 1Ch This field identifies the end of the presentation header when looking at message traces.

Field Data

The Field Data is the most important part for flexibility in the message format.

The method described here allows great benefits, but there is a price to pay for this flexibility; each field element has 2 or 5 bytes of overhead.

The benefits gained from this overhead are:

  • Ability to pass binary data

New features such as Signature Capture will require passing large amounts of data. The overhead required if this cannot be passed as binary data is very high.

  • Variable Length Data Fields.
  • The data is fairly readable on a message trace.

The Field Data consists of 0 or more Field Elements, arranged one after the other in the message.

Field Data Format

The fields comprising the Field Element are arranged in the following order.

The fields are described below

Field Bytes Value Use
Field Type 2 Indicates the type of data that is included in this field element. This is an alphanumeric field. Characters 0-9 and AZ are available for use. The table in section lists the available values.
LLLL 2 Indicates the length in bytes of the data to follow. Length can have a value from 0000 to a value that will not cause the total message to exceed the maximum size allowed for the implementation. Available values for this are detailed in section. LLLL is transmitted in BCD (Binary Coded Decimal) form. The most significant byte is transmitted first, followed by the least significant byte. For example, a length of 256 bytes will be transmitted as 02h 56h.
Data LLLL The data for this field. If no data is in this field (for example, when the functionality is indicated by the field type on its own), there will be no data.
Field Separator 1 1Ch This field is used to make it easier to identify the end of a field element when looking at message traces.

Extra Field Separators

Some POS implementations will be easier to develop this interface if field data appears in a particular order, with additional field separators to represent fields that are missing.

To support this, it is acceptable to include extra Field Separator characters (1Ch) between Field Elements.

This can be easily supported in the parsing routine by ignoring any Field Separator characters when it is expecting the first character of the Field Type.

TRANSACTION CODES

  • Each transaction code is identified with a two character code. Characters 0-9, and A-Z are available for use in the Transaction Code.
Transaction Code Description
20 Sale
70 Sale Alipay/Wechat/QR Payment/Other wallet Transaction
26 Void
27 Refund
34 Balance inquiry
41 Installment
43 Redemption
50 Settlement
71 Void transaction by trace number
72 Void transaction by reference 1
EA Sale + E-TAX
EB Sale Wallet + E-TAX
ED Installment + E-TAX
EF Void + E-TAX
EH Create E-TAX
EI Void E-TAX Only
EJ E-TAX Inquiry (All Hosts)
EL E-TAX Inquiry (Single transaction)
EK Settlement E-TAX

FILED TYPES

  • Each different type of Field Element within the Field Data is designated by a different Field Type value. Each Field Type also has an attribute and a length associated with it. The length may be a single number, which indicates a fixed length field, or a variable length which indicates a maximum length. Variable length fields are indicated by two dots preceding the length. **For example, ** Track 1 data is a variable length field up to 76 characters long, which has a length description of ..76.
  • Field Types are alphanumeric, meaning 0-9 and A-Z are valid characters in the Field Type.

Field Attributes

The following table lists the different field attributes available for use in the Field Type Definition Table.

Attribute Description

Attribute Descrition
ANS Alpha, Numeric and Special characters
AN Alpha and Numeric character
N Numeric characters
Z Numeric Data plus ‘=’ character This is used for Track 2 data, where the ‘=’ is the separator between the card number and the rest of the data.
N Amount. Numeric characters indicating number of cents. No $ sign or decimal point is included.
B Binary Data The data is a stream of bytes that could take any value.
T Telephone Number Data Valid characters are 0-9, *, #, space, -, and a comma or a P for a dial tone pause.

    E-TAX Field Type Definitions

    Field Type Attribute Length Field Data
    U1 ANS 20 Unique ID

    Use for Transaction Reference between EDC and POS
    Example Format : YYYYMMDDHHmmss + Random 6 digits
    V1 ANS 10 **Optional
    VAT Amount
    V2 ANS 10 **Optional
    TAX Allowance
    V3 ANS 20 **Optional
    Merchant Unique Value
    V4 ANS 6 **Optional
    Campaign Type
    EP ANS 11 Total E-TAX Transactions. Including 3 type,
    - Total E-TAX Transaction
    - Total Success
    - Total Failed.
    Each type has 3 digits padding with 0 and separated with | ("Simple pipe", 7C)
    ET ANS ..65535 E-TAX Data Block

    Completed E-TAX Data Block generated by POS regards of the E-TAX Specification
    EQ ANS ..65535 E-TAX Transaction Status. Each Transaction has include 3 Elements,
    - Transaction Unique ID (U1)
    - Document Type
    - Status (PENDING, SUCCESS or NOT_SUCCESS)

    Each Element has variable length and separate with , ("Comma", 2C)

    Each Transactions has variable length and separate with | ("Simple pipe", 7C)

    Field Requirements

    Request Meaning Description
    M Mandatory Field Important field that is required to send/receive.
    O Optional Field Field to send/receive but not required.
    C Conditional Field Field is only required under certain conditions.

    Bank ID

    The following table lists the identities of the banks in case of ECR client wants to do cross-bank transaction.
    The Bank ID will be present for every message in optional when ECR want to process for the specific bank, or can be absent if multiple bank application installed and wants EDC to launch the payment screen and manual selection by POS Staffs.

    Bank IDs

    ID Refers to Bank
    01 Bank of Thailand (BOT)
    02 Bangkok Bank Public Complany Limited (BBL)
    04 Kasikorn Bank Company Limited
    06 Krung Thai Bank Public Company Limited (KTB)
    11 TMB Bank Public Company Limited ( TMB)
    14 Siam Commercial Bank Public Company Limited (SCB)
    24 United Overseas Bank (Thai) PCL (UOBT)
    25 Bank of Ayudhya Public Company Limited (BAY)
    30 Government Saving Bank (GOV)

    33 Government Housing Bank (GHB)
    34 BANK FOR AGRICULTURE AND AGRICULTURAL COOPERATIVES
    39 Mizuho Bank Bangkok Branch (MHCB)
    00 Undefined, if this value presents, EDC will threat as no Bank selection and will prompt / Auto select the bank according to the card inserted / bank selection in EDC Screen
    • Please note that not all Bank ID is supported and some of supported Bank may not appeared in specs. POS engineer need to confirm the bank id with Main Acquirer if POS need to use this field.

    Payment Indicator (PI)

    The Payment Indicator used to indicates payment method which allows POS select transaction type by theirself. POS is possibly sent this field when do Sale (Transaction code = 20) to indicate which type of payment supported by terminal POS need to do.

    Indicators

    ID Refers to Payment Method
    00 or absent Card Type, Full Payment
    01 Card Type, Uplan
    02 Card Type, Pre-authorization
    03 Card Type, Completion
    04 Card Type, DCC
    • Please note that not all Bank ID is supported and some of supported Bank may not appeared in specs. POS engineer need to confirm the bank id with Main Acquirer if POS need to use this field.

    RESPONSE CODES

    The following table lists the response codes that the Terminal will send back to the POS in a response message.

    Response Code Meaning
    00 Approved
    Transaction is approved by ECR / host
    ND Declined
    The transaction is declined. More explanation is included in the response text filed.
    If any activity is time out, EDC will sends only ND to POS
    NB No Batch
    The batch is empty when doing settlement.

    5. Sale Wallet(Transaction Code = 70)

    Transaction Flow

    This command include AliPay, WeChat, KPlus, QR Credit application

    Example Request Alipay : 02004236303030303030303030313037303030311C343000123030303030303030313030301C4131000230311C0308

    EDC sends data to POS (EDC -> POS)

    1. If EDC got the request message from POS, EDC will send ACK message(0x06). but if EDC busy at the moment EDC will send NAK message(0x15)
    2. If payment process success EDC will return reponse as the table below.

    17. Sale + E-TAX (Transaction Code = EA)

    In case POS does not sends buyer's email address to EDC, EDC must display Interface to fill-in email address. If merchant would like to void this transaction, they must use only Void + E-TAX, void transaction only is not allowed. There are three scenarios for this service, which are

    Full Info from POS
    Onec, received full info from POS, EDC sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Insert ID Card
    Inform customer to inserts their ID Card, after EDC reads the ID Card, EDC will sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Static QR
    EDC Informs customer to insert their ID card, If customer choose to fill information later, then EDC sends Incomplete E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval and prints QR slip containing E-TAX’s URL

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    Field Type Attribute Length Request Data Example
    40 ANS 12 M Amount Transaction 000000010000
    R1 ANS 20 O Reference 1 Reference 1
    R2 ANS 20 O Reference 2 Reference 2
    U1 ANS 20 M Unique ID

    Use for Transaction Reference between EDC and POS
    Example Format : YYYYMMDDHHmmss + Random 6 digits    		 20240828143230123456
    V1 ANS 10 O VAT Amount 0000001000
    V2 ANS 10 O TAX Allowance 0000001000
    V3 ANS 20 O Merchant Unique Value Merchant UV 1
    V4 ANS 6 O Campaign Type
    ET ANS ..65535 M E-TAX Data Block

    Completed E-TAX Data Block generated by POS regards of the E-TAX Specification

    18. Sale Wallet + E-TAX (Transaction Code = EB)

    In case POS does not sends buyer's email address to EDC, EDC must display Interface to fill-in email address. If merchant would like to void this transaction, they must use only Void + E-TAX, void transaction only is not allowed. There are three scenarios for this service, which are

    Full Info from POS
    Onec, received full info from POS, EDC sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Insert ID Card
    Inform customer to inserts their ID Card, after EDC reads the ID Card, EDC will sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Static QR
    EDC Informs customer to insert their ID card, If customer choose to fill information later, then EDC sends Incomplete E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval and prints QR slip containing E-TAX’s URL

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    Field Type Attribute Length Request Data Example
    40 ANS 12 M Amount Transaction 000000010000
    A1 ANS 2 M Wallet Type

    AliPay = 01
    WeChat = 02
    Thai QR Payment = 03
    QR Credit = 04    		 03

    R2 ANS 20 O Reference 2 Reference 2

    20. Void + E-TAX (Transaction Code = EF)

    Void + E-TAX will be used only when Sale + E-TAX was issued for that transaction. If only E-TAX has been issue, then uses Void E-TAX Only to cancel an E-TAX transaction.

    Exception cases :

    1. If Void + E-TAX fails to void the transaction part, then no need to do anything further.

    2. If Void + E-TAX fails to void E-TAX part, a user must issues Void + E-TAX or Void E-TAX Only again

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    Field Type Attribute Length Request Data Example
    U1 ANS 20 M Unique ID

    21. Create E-TAX (Transaction Code = EH)

    This service use when creating only E-TAX, such as merchant receives cash payment or issues E-TAX replacement. And if user wants to void that transaction, Void E-TAX Only must be issued. There are three scenarios for this service, which are

    Full Info from POS
    Onec, received full info from POS, EDC sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Insert ID Card
    Inform customer to inserts their ID Card, after EDC reads the ID Card, EDC will sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Static QR
    EDC Informs customer to insert their ID card, If customer choose to fill information later, then EDC sends Incomplete E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval and prints QR slip containing E-TAX’s URL

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    Field Type Attribute Length Request Data Example
    U1 ANS 20 M Unique ID

    Use for Transaction Reference between EDC and POS
    Example Format : YYYYMMDDHHmmss + Random 6 digits    		 00000000000000000001

    22. Void E-TAX Only (Transaction Code = EI)

    Use when Void + E-TAX fails to void the E-TAX part or merchant would like to void Create E-TAX transaction.

    Exception timeout

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    Message Structure

    The messages that are transmitted omn the link between the POSNET and EDC will use the following structure

    Field Bytes Value Comment
    STX 1 02 or 82 Start of Text Char (02) = ASCII 02 for start of text. This character is used to indicate the start of frame.

    ASCII 02 for start of text in normal transaction.
    ASCII 82 for start of text in [E-TAX] transaction.
    Transaction Type 4 Type of transaction 4 digits as ACSII to mention the type of transaction, can see more details from Transaction Types
    Length 3 Length of MESSAGE DATA (3 digits as ACSII) Actual length of data by excluding neither checksum nor end of text.

    for [E-TAX] : (3 bytes as base 16) Actual length of data by excluding neither checksum nor end of text.
    For example, a length of 256 bytes will be convert to base 16 and transmitted as 000100.
    MESSAGE DATA Variable Data field follow by Transaction Type rule.
    LRC 1 This character is calculated by exclusive OR-ing all data start from STX until last byte of data field using LRC.
    ETX 1 03 End of Text Char (03) = ASCII 03 for end of text. It is included as an extra check that the message was successfully received and that the receiver is in synchronization with the transmitted message.

    Transaction Types

    Each transaction type is identified with a four characters. Characters 0-9, and A-Z are available for use in the Transaction Type.

    Transaction Types Meaning
    SALE Sale
    Transaction code = 20
    QR
    Transaction code = 70
    VOID Void
    Transaction code = 26
    SETT Settlement
    Transaction code = 50
    ETAX E-TAX
    Transaction code
    - EA = Sale + E-TAX
    - EB = Sale Wallet + E-TAX
    - ED = Installment + E-TAX
    - EF = Void + E-TAX
    - EH = Create E-TAX
    - EI = Void E-TAX Only
    - EJ = E-TAX Inquiry (All Hosts)
    - EL = E-TAX Inquiry (Single Transaction)
    - EK = Settlement E-TAX

    FILED TYPES

    • Base on LinkPos HyperCom and field types
    • Field Types are alphanumeric, meaning 0-9 and A-Z are valid characters in the Field Type.

    Field Attributes

    The following table lists the different field attributes available for use in the Field Type Definition Table.

    Attribute Description

    Attribute Descrition
    ANS Alpha, Numeric and Special characters
    AN Alpha and Numeric character
    N Numeric characters
    Z Numeric Data plus ‘=’ character This is used for Track 2 data, where the ‘=’ is the separator between the card number and the rest of the data.
    N Amount. Numeric characters indicating number of cents. No $ sign or decimal point is included.
    B Binary Data The data is a stream of bytes that could take any value.
    T Telephone Number Data Valid characters are 0-9, *, #, space, -, and a comma or a P for a dial tone pause.

    Field Type Definition

    The following table lists the defined additional field type definitions with their attributes, and the lengths of each field.

    Field Type Attribute Length Field Data
    P1 ANS 2 Response Code
    P2 N 4 Settlement Sale Count
    P3 N 12 Settlement Total Sale
    P4 N 4 Transaction NII
    P5 ANS 16 Transaction Response Text
    P6 ANS 20 Card No
    P7 ANS 22 Card Holder Name

    QR Field Type Definitions

    Field Type Attribute Length Field Data
    A1 Ans 2 “WL” - Alipay/WeChat (select source of fund on EDC)
    “QR” - Thai QR Payment
    “QC” - QR Credit
    “QP” - QR Payment

    E-TAX Field Type Definitions

    Field Type Attribute Length Field Data
    ANS 2 E-TAX Transaction Type

    - EA = Sale + E-TAX
    - EB = Sale Wallet + E-TAX
    - ED = Installment + E-TAX
    - EF = Void + E-TAX
    - EH = Create E-TAX
    - EI = Void E-TAX Only
    - EJ = E-TAX Inquiry (All Hosts)
    - EL = E-TAX Inquiry (Single Transaction)
    - EK = Settlement E-TAX
    U1 ANS 20 Unique ID

    Use for Transaction Reference between EDC and POS
    Example Format : YYYYMMDDHHmmss + Random 6 digits
    V1 ANS 10 **Optional
    VAT Amount
    V2 ANS 10 **Optional
    TAX Allowance
    V3 ANS 20 **Optional
    Merchant Unique Value
    V4 ANS 6 **Optional
    Campaign Type
    EP ANS 11 Total E-TAX Transactions. Including 3 type,
    - Total E-TAX Transaction
    - Total Success
    - Total Failed.
    Each type has 3 digits padding with 0 and separated with | ("Simple pipe", 7C)
    ET ANS ..65535 E-TAX Data Block

    Completed E-TAX Data Block generated by POS regards of the E-TAX Specification
    EQ ANS ..65535 E-TAX Transaction Status. Each Transaction has include 3 Elements,
    - Transaction Unique ID (U1)
    - Document Type
    - Status (PENDING, SUCCESS or NOT_SUCCESS)

    Each Element has variable length and separate with , ("Comma", 2C)

    Each Transactions has variable length and separate with | ("Simple pipe", 7C)

    Field Requirements

    Request Meaning Description
    M Mandatory Field Important field that is required to send/receive.
    O Optional Field Field to send/receive but not required.
    C Conditional Field Field is only required under certain conditions.

    4. Settlement (Transaction Type - SETT)

    (1)

    Response Code
    (2)    		 Batch No.
    (6)    		 Sale Count
    (3)    		 Total Sale Amount
    (12)    		 NII
    (3)    		 Batch Settle Status

    Field Type Attribute Length Data Example Value Example

    ANS 4 Transaction Type SETT 53 45 54 54
    N 3 Length 107 31 30 37
    P1 ANS 2 Response Code 00 30 30
    50 N 6 Batch No. 000012 30 30 30 30 31 32

    P3 N 12 Total Sale Amount 15000.00 = 000001500000 30 30 30 30 30 31 35 30 30 30 30 30
    HN N 3 NII 130 31 33 30
    ZZ ANS 80 Batch Settle Status Format: Host Index(3)+NII(3)+SettlementStatus(2)

    N 1 ETX 03

    16. Sale + E-TAX (Transaction Code = ETAX)

    In case POS does not sends buyer's email address to EDC, EDC must display Interface to fill-in email address. If merchant would like to void this transaction, they must use only Void + E-TAX, void transaction only is not allowed. There are three scenarios for this service, which are

    Full Info from POS
    Onec, received full info from POS, EDC sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Insert ID Card
    Inform customer to inserts their ID Card, after EDC reads the ID Card, EDC will sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Static QR
    EDC Informs customer to insert their ID card, If customer choose to fill information later, then EDC sends Incomplete E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval and prints QR slip containing E-TAX’s URL

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    (1)    		 ETX

    17. Sale Wallet + E-TAX (Transaction Code = ETAX)

    In case POS does not sends buyer's email address to EDC, EDC must display Interface to fill-in email address. If merchant would like to void this transaction, they must use only Void + E-TAX, void transaction only is not allowed. There are three scenarios for this service, which are

    Full Info from POS
    Onec, received full info from POS, EDC sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Insert ID Card
    Inform customer to inserts their ID Card, after EDC reads the ID Card, EDC will sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Static QR
    EDC Informs customer to insert their ID card, If customer choose to fill information later, then EDC sends Incomplete E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval and prints QR slip containing E-TAX’s URL

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    19. Void + E-TAX (Transaction Code = ETAX)

    Void + E-TAX will be used only when Sale + E-TAX was issued for that transaction. If only E-TAX has been issue, then uses Void E-TAX Only to cancel an E-TAX transaction.

    Exception cases :

    1. If Void + E-TAX fails to void the transaction part, , then no need to do anything further.

    2. If Void + E-TAX fails to void E-TAX part, a user must issues Void + E-TAX or Void E-TAX Only again

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    20. Create E-TAX (Transaction Code = ETAX)

    This service use when creating only E-TAX, such as merchant receives cash payment or issues E-TAX replacement. And if user wants to void that transaction, Void E-TAX Only must be issued. There are three scenarios for this service, which are

    Full Info from POS
    Onec, received full info from POS, EDC sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Insert ID Card
    Inform customer to inserts their ID Card, after EDC reads the ID Card, EDC will sends E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval, then prints E-TAX receipt

    Static QR
    EDC Informs customer to insert their ID card, If customer choose to fill information later, then EDC sends Incomplete E-TAX Data to PCC for Approval and prints QR slip containing E-TAX’s URL

    POS sends request to EDC(POS -> EDC)

    STX
    (1)    		 Transaction Type
    (4)    		 Length
    (3)    		 E-TAX Transaction Type
    (2)    		 Unique ID
    (20)    		 E-TAX Data Block
    (..65535)    		 LRC
    (1)    		 ETX
    (1)

    ANS 4 M Transaction Type ETAX 45 54 41 58
